title: Merry Chrismoose . .
description:
JLS Photography - Alaska posted a photo:

We always have moose visits at Christmas time. Yesterday two very large cow moose tramped through the deep snow looking for a nice place to chomp on some willow. This moose was only about twenty feet from our cabin window - so all I had to do to capture to her was throw open the window and snap away. I tried talking to her, but she totally ignored me. Since it was about minus 14 F. degrees outside at the time - I quickly closed the window and let her dine in peace. She did however wish everyone a very Merry Chrismoose.
author: nobody@flickr.com ("JLS Photography - Alaska")
